                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13239792" author="jcoveney" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 19:27:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Good catch, Andy! I assume that the feature is used in normal HBase operations, just counterproductive in MR jobs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239872" author="alindeman" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 20:53:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;My understanding is that the block cache is not very useful (and actually harmful because of the wasted cycles populating it and evicting it) when scanning through large numbers of rows that will only be needed once in a map-reduce job.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13239874" author="alindeman" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2012 20:54:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;But yah, under circumstances like random access, it&apos;s useful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13240034" author="jcoveney" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2012 00:00:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Andy,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for adding this! Always nice to bring things in line. Committed to 0.10 and 0.11, r1306041 and r1306042 respectively. Testing against 0.9&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13240059" author="jcoveney" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2012 00:34:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied to 0.9, r1306058.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13240397" author="alindeman" created="Wed, 28 Mar 2012 14:26:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the fast turn around!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
